target_assessment.type_match_reasoning: No findings were reported, so the target vulnerability was not identified.

notes: The audit verdict was 'safe' with 0 findings, but the ground truth indicates a cross-function reentrancy vulnerability in the borrow function. The vulnerability exists because borrow sends ETH (line 68) before the final health check (line 71), and during this external call, the attacker can re-enter to call exitMarket (line 74), which sets inMarket[msg.sender] = false (line 76). This bypasses the health check on line 71 because isHealthy returns false early if !inMarket[account] (line 51). The audit missed this critical vulnerability.
